<MyContainer >
<p>You can also wrap anything in a Razor component, like this custom container. By specifying a container name (note it must be in camelCase), you can create custom containers.</p>
<pre><code class="language-markdown">:::myContainer
This is a custom container.
:::
</code></pre>
<p>Blake will render this as:</p>
<pre><code class="language-razor">&lt;MyContainer&gt;
This is a custom container.
&lt;/MyContainer&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>The rest is up to Blazor - just make sure you have a component named <code>MyContainer</code> in your project, with a <code>RenderFragment</code> parameter for the content.
You can see the example <code>MyContainer</code> component that was generated by Blake in the <code>Components</code> folder of this project.</p>
</MyContainer>
